  "prompt": "How do I remove the Google Docs header while sharing a file?",
  "response": "Here's how to remove the header when sharing a Google Docs file:\n\n1. Open the Google Docs file\n2. Go to \"View\" in the top menu\n3. Select \"Print layout\" to see the header\n4. Click directly on the header\n5. Delete the text or select and backspace\n6. Save the document\n\nAlternatively:\n- If you want to completely remove header formatting:\n1. Go to \"Insert\" > \"Header & page number\" > \"Remove header\"\n\nWhen sharing the file, the header will no longer appear. If you're specifically sharing a PDF version, use \"File\" > \"Download\" > \"PDF Document\" to share without the header.",
